{"word":"πλούσιος","slug":"πλούσιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πλούσιος</b></el> <el>(πλούσιος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>πλοῦτος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>rich, wealthy, opulent</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>rich in</i> a thing, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>dives opum</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of things, <i>richly furnished, ample, abundant</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ίως</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}